<br>
1) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Regarding soloing with charm</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
For a mage it really is quite useless as a soloing tool, unless you plan on training everyone in bot every 15 minutes and have access to buffs from death (hint: no one in bot will want to buff you after youve repeatedly trained them :P). <br>
Yes it is quite possible to kill <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>something</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> solo -- in fact one time i killed 3 things solo back to back. No, it is not feasable to do it consistantly without the assistance of at least a botted support class to reduce enemy dps. This is because eventually, charm <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>will break</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> while you are fighting, and when that happens you are in all likelyhood going to die. <br>
There just is simply no way a 65 mage can live through a charm break <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>and</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the enemy mob beating you up at once without someone to heal you or help mitigate that damage (through stuns, snare, root, runes, ect). You will die too often to make it a worth while venture. However, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>partnering</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with several classes is quite feasable.<br>
<br>
2) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Regarding maintaining a charm pet indefinately.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> A pet <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>can</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be maintained indefinately if you have a good cleric in your group and elemental silence. <br>
Even still, it is quite risky for a mage, since we are so heavily dependant on others to mitigate damage unlike the other 3 charm classes. <br>
Maintaining a pet is virtually effortless if someone in your group can snare and is feeding you runes. Also, making pathing and distance work to your advantage, even unsnared, is key to mitigating ex-pet damage (i find it quite ironic that a game flaw which plagued us so long, is now advantageous <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
3) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Regarding charm pet strength</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. It all depends on how much you buff it. How much you can buff your pet while still being able to manage it depends on the skill of the player, the class in question, and the skill of your groupmates. Typically i as a mage with humble equipment (unbuffed 2100 hp) will give my pet a set of weapons and use bo1 on it, which is fairly manageable for me. This results in it doing a dps of about 350ish (not counting charm breaks during battle, which would lower its dps). <br>
If i am grouped with an excellent cleric, or a snare class, i will buff my pet higher. But usually that is the buffs i use on my pet. If im grouped with a crappy or occupied cleric, i just use an unbuffed pet.<br>
