<br>
3) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>My impressions of mage charm.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Honestly i feel our charm is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>mostly</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> balanced, granted the risks and situational element involved for a mage. It is clearly the least overpowered of all 4 classes charm spells, but none the less it does need changing.<br>
<br>
4) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>What should be done.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> There are a few things which in my opinion would completely balance the charm line, and almost unfortunatley none of them are being implemented on test <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
Simply have the charm spell put an effect on both the mob, and caster, which gives the following effects:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>When charm is applied to a mob...</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
...It cannot be hasted nor given weapons. The natrual dps of a mob is quite enough reward for the risk. <br>
<br>
...Overwrites all snares on the mob. Snare trivializes the risk of charm completely (im speaking from experiance here!) and it is absurd to allow charmed mobs be snared. <br>
<br>
...A buff on the caster will overwrite any and all rune spells. High level runes mitigate the risk of charm far too much (again speaking from experiance).<br>
<br>
<br>
5) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>What not to do to fix charm.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
-Please do not decrease the duration or resistibility of charm spells (which is the direction i unfortunately see you going). Charm breaks frequently enough, and if it were to break more often than it does it (for a mage at least), it wouldnt be worth the risk and cause frustration to both the mage and their healer. <br>
<br>
If you really must limit the amount of time a charm pet is kept, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>do it through recast delays</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. That would be a much wiser solution, since it would involve more casters while causing less frustration.<br>
